7517056136470646030.transcript: If you're like me and you love a good sweet treat, here are five bakeries to add to your New York City hit list. First up is the Filipina-owned Cora Bakery over in Sunnyside, Queens. They specialize in donuts like this ube one, but don't skip out on their other things like their banana cookie or their matcha cruller. Next up is Honey's Bakery over in Aster Place. This was my number one bakery of 2024 for good reason. Everything here is executed to perfection, but don't skip their carrot cake. Next up is the newly opened Birdie Bakery over in Williamsburg. They have some expertly handcrafted sweet treats that are simple yet delicious. Definitely recommend checking out their alfajor or their strawberry tart that is in season, and it is one of my favorite bites. Another bakery that I love in Williamsburg is Ceremonia Bake Shop. I love their banana nut loaf as well as their chocolate chip cookie and jalapeno cornbread, but if I'm going there, I am going for that breakfast burrito. It is one of my favorites in Williamsburg and one of the most popular in New York City right now. And last up, we have Welcome Home over in Bed-Stuy, which has without a doubt one of my favorite cinnamon rolls in New York City, as well as a delicious take on pigs in a blanket. And those are just some of my favorite bakeries in New York City right now. If you like this roundup, follow along as I try every other bakery in New York City.
